TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 

Suppose \[f(x) =  \frac{7x+2}{x^2+x-2}.\]

$BR 
Then

\[f(x) = \frac{A}{x-1} + \frac{B}{x+2}\]
where



A =  \{ ans_rule(10) \} and 
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(3));


TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
B =  \{ ans_rule(10) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp(4));



SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
Since
\[ \frac{A}{x-1} + \frac{B}{x+2} = \frac{A(x+2)+B(x-1)}{(x-1)(x+2)}\]
and
\[(x-1)(x+2) = x^2+x-2\]
we must have
\[A(x+2)+B(x-1) = 7x+2\]
for all real numbers \(x\).  Setting \(x=-2\) gives
\[-3B = -12\] or 
\[B=4.\]
Setting \(x= 1\) gives 
\[3A = 9\]
or 
\[A=3.\]
EOT


